# Example UDS session for analyzer fixture tests.
# Format: [Req]/[Resp] with bare hex bytes (reqresp format).
# Covers: DSC, SecurityAccess (with RTDNE + wrong key + successful unlock),
# RDBI (VIN), WDBI, RoutineControl (general programming failure), ECUReset.

# 1. Switch to extended diagnostic session.
[Req] 10 03
[Resp] 50 03 00 19 01 F4

# 2. SecurityAccess seed request — ECU is still in its post-boot delay window.
[Req] 27 01
[Resp] 7F 27 37

# 3. Retry seed request after the delay — ECU returns a seed.
[Req] 27 01
[Resp] 67 01 AA BB CC DD

# 4. Send a wrong key — ECU rejects with Invalid Key.
[Req] 27 02 00 00 00 00
[Resp] 7F 27 35

# 5. Request a fresh seed and send the correct key — ECU unlocks.
[Req] 27 01
[Resp] 67 01 11 22 33 44
[Req] 27 02 DE AD BE EF
[Resp] 67 02

# 6. Read VIN via RDBI 0xF190 — ASCII "1C4HJXFG5KW501234".
[Req] 22 F1 90
[Resp] 62 F1 90 31 43 34 48 4A 58 46 47 35 4B 57 35 30 31 32 33 34

# 7. Write VIN via WDBI 0xF190 — ECU accepts.
[Req] 2E F1 90 31 43 34 48 4A 58 46 47 35 4B 57 35 30 31 32 33 34
[Resp] 6E F1 90

# 8. Start a routine (e.g. erase flash) — ECU returns General Programming Failure.
[Req] 31 01 FF 00
[Resp] 7F 31 72

# 9. Hard ECU reset.
[Req] 11 01
[Resp] 51 01
